                <h1>Understanding Proliferative Endometrium: Key Insights</h1>
                <p>Proliferative endometrium is a phase of the menstrual cycle characterized by the thickening of the endometrial lining. This occurs due to the influence of estrogen and prepares the uterus for potential implantation of an embryo. Understanding this phase is crucial for assessing fertility and diagnosing endometrial disorders.</p>
